Post more, make more money, and stress less!

✅ Have you been spending too much time on Instagram lately? Maybe you are trying to consistently create new content every day, but deep down you really want to do something different.

✨Let me share you 4 ways to spend less time on social media.

🧠 Tip 1. Set Goals for yourself!
Setting goals encourages you to create the content you've always wanted to and feel proud when you achieve it. So, make the most of your time and stay focused by setting goals for yourself—it'll be worth it! e.g. what’s the purpose of your content? To build authority? boost engagement? or to increase leads?

🧠 Tip 2. Research, research, and reserach! 
☑ Find a viral topic in 2 mins! 
☑ Go to Google > add chrome extension “ViralFindr” > you can use upto 3 trial for free > lists top 3 ideal competitors & anaylize viral content
☑ Be a creator rather than consuming!

🧠 Tip 3. Use aesthetic customizable templates 
Easy-to-use Template will help you save hours of time and create a perfect, professional-looking, cohesive feed in minutes. You don't have to spend a lot of time creating each post from scratch.

🧠 Tip 4. Use Scheduler ➡️ Story + Carousels post
📲 Download Meta Business Suite app (FREE) and schedule for your IG Story and static posts

〰️ Make a goal like 4 reels + 2 carousels per week 〰️ Schedule 1 or 2 stories before the following day
The great thing is Meta has a great analytic insight and shows the best time posting static posts and story.

☁️ Here’s what I am doing for content creation 
➕ Story & Carousels = Schedule Meta Business Suite 
➕ Reel: edit reels with trending audios and save draft and post manually at my best post time

HERE 👇🏻👇🏻
SAVE it for later so that you know what to find your content ideas 🤍

Have you run out of content ideas and your brain is so messy and draining? Don't worry, you aren't alone, I've been there too!

🧠 Here are my top 10 methods for finding unlimited content ideas!

1. Pinterest
☑ It’s my go to method for inspiration and ideas, but also to learn!
I usually save as many as I can and then research one by one.

2. Competitor profiles
☑ Analyze their highest performing content and look at the comments. Find out what their audience is talking about/requesting..

3. Your audience
☑ You can ask your followers to vote in your stories or pay attention to what they ask about in your DMs

4. TikTok
☑ Go to google & add chrome extension “Sort TikTok”
☑ Benefits - you’ll get idea inspiration / hooks/ caption & keywords

5. Competitor’s YouTube Channels
☑ Another tip: Add “YouTube Summary with ChatGPT & Claude" (Google Chrome extension) to get the summary of long form videos!

6. Answer the public and Google trends
☑ If you enter 1-2 keywords, it will display the top Google searches for those keywords.

7. Facebook groups and Reddit forums
☑ People often ask questions and discuss topics.

8. Quora
☑ Gather frequently asked questions and resource recommendations on a topic

9. Google
☑ I use Google to learn and get more ideas from blogs, articles and even just find some keywords. Google Search Suggestions can give you keywords ideas

10. Keywords everywhere
☑ This Chrome Extension helps you brainstorm topic titles, identify subtopics, and generate topics.

🫶 Share with others who need these information!

🤍 Comment 'CLUB', and I'll send you the step-by-step content process that took me from a 9-5 job to being a financially and time-free boss girl in business✨

➪ B-roll: 7 SECONDS LONG
➪ Tutorial: 17 to 27 SECONDS

📣 Understanding your competitors and how you can learn from them.
I told my clients and students so many times.
↳ Collect top 5 competitors (more than 50k followers) in your niche
↳ Keep an eye on their content & study it (Use Metricool or Viralfindr)
↳ Re-create on your way (remember it is not copy directly. It’s just inspiration)

📣 New algorithm alert - 
 IG does not care about
↳ Not Save ❌
↳ Not Like ❌

INSTEAD! 
3 types of engagement IG is focused on: 
1. Get people to SHRAE your content. SHARE = 400 views 
This means you need to create shareable content such as entertaining, newsworthy, or informative content.
2. Get people to FOLLOW you.
If people follow you, then your content will be showing more!
3. Get people to comment your content by using ManyChat.
e.g. "Comment [insert your offer name] then I'll send you my FREE [insert your freebie name]"

📣 I stopped posting every day. 
Instead, I focus on my business and post content 3-4 times a week. It helps me to create high-quality content that brings me tons of new followers and clients every single day.

📣 I don’t care about hashtags / what time to post / how many times to post per day. What matters is how you can stay consistent with your own goal. 

Think big!

Is your reel stuck at 200 to 500 views? 😮‍💨

No worries! ✨ I am telling you everything my proven strategies so that you can get out of 200 view jail and find dreamy clients.

Your struggle 1️⃣

✅ “I am not gaining new followers”

1. Add a REASON to follow you by optimizing your bio clearly e.g. “I help XYZ…” | “Helping you to ____, let me solve your problem.”
2. Post more GROWTH CONTENT TYPES

→ 2 ways to figure out your Ta’s pain points & needs: 1) asking audience by using a poll 2) analyzing your competitor’s website 

Your struggle 2️⃣

✅ “I am not making any sales.” 

DO THIS 👇
1. Offer a IRRESISTIBLE FREEBIE that leads into your paid offer. A free guide, template, training, course, tutorial, checklist, etc.
→ e.g. I offer my free weekly content planner so that not only my reel went viral and get more reach but also more sales and clients.

2. Use your STORIES to talk about this freebie and show BTS of your business

3. GIVE GIVE GIVE GIVE…..ASK! : "Think about you are a boxer, Your Jab = your free content & Right hook = asking audiences your paid offer" - Gary Vaynerchuck - 

→  you give a jab jab jab and then use right hook = your CTAs 

4. Keep monitoring and adjusting your strategy of movement: Again, Let’s say you’re a fighter and you keep punching the opponent but if your strategy is not working, change your tactics right away.
